# JavaScript – Async JS: Callbacks, Promises, Async/Await & Fetch

---

## 📘 Why Async JavaScript?

JavaScript is **single-threaded** — it can only do one thing at a time. Async programming lets JS start a long task (API call, timer) and continue running other code while waiting for the result.

```
Synchronous (blocking):   Task1 → Task2 → Task3
Asynchronous (non-blocking): Start Task1 → Start Task2 → Task1 done → Task2 done
```

