## 📞 Callbacks

A callback is a **function passed as an argument** to another function, called after an operation completes.

```js
function fetchData(callback) {
  setTimeout(() => {
    const data = { id: 1, name: "Ali" };
    callback(data);
  }, 1000);
}

fetchData((data) => {
  console.log(data.name);  // "Ali"
});
```

### Callback Hell (the problem)
```js
// Nested callbacks become unreadable
getUser(userId, (user) => {
  getPosts(user.id, (posts) => {
    getComments(posts[0].id, (comments) => {
      getLikes(comments[0].id, (likes) => {
        // 😱 Pyramid of doom
      });
    });
  });
});
```

