## 🔁 Event Loop (How Async Works)

```
Call Stack → Web APIs → Callback Queue → Event Loop → Call Stack
```

```js
console.log("1");              // sync — runs first

setTimeout(() => {
  console.log("2");            // async — queued
}, 0);

Promise.resolve().then(() => {
  console.log("3");            // microtask — runs before timeout
});

console.log("4");              // sync — runs second

// Output: 1 → 4 → 3 → 2
```

> **Microtask queue** (Promises) has higher priority than the **macrotask queue** (setTimeout, setInterval).

